If you mean Wu's fighting gear it is more of matter of coin (pp) then level unfortunately.

It would be nice if Monk's could make these items at about a lvl they can use them but I think with the bazaar and the availability of cheaper items making these probably does not make sense.

However this is all speculation as I do not have a monk and am not sure what compairable items cost.  But I have seen the Wu's stuff running for 20 to 50 pp in the bazaar, it will cost you MUCH more than that to make it yourself.  A lot of that cost is getting to the stage where you can make it.

Their are better guides but the Wu's Fighting gear recipies are

pattern       (&lt; 1 gp)
viscous mana  (~ 7-10 pp bought from a chanter)
4 heady kiola (~ 1gp if you make them ~4pp if you buy)
  2 kiola sap, 1 water, 1 bottle, 
  mid 40's brewing skill
1,2,3 silk swatch(s) (depending on pattern)

The tailoring skill needed is in the 135 to 155 range so you will probably need to go the crystalline silk route or medium pelt route to get that high.

For me the problem was silk, it was expensive to buy in the bazaar and very tedious to get myself.  I had good luck collecting crystalline silk in the crystal caves but it was still slow going.

